Patients included in this study were aged from 1 month to 9 years. The median age was 3 years. RSV was more frequent in younger children (p
 = 10−7) with 12 out of 23 virus-positive cases from 6 months to 2 years age group. No IAV or IBV infection was detected in children younger than 1-year old (Table 4
). Only 8 patients from 1 to 6 months age group were enrolled in the study.
